  "text": "Studies showed that piglets of sows fed diets supplemented with L-carnitine grow faster during the suckling period than piglets of control sows fed diets without L-carnitine. Lcarnitine-treated sows had larger litters and higher litter weights than control sows. Also, milk of L-carnitine-treated sows had higher concentrations of total and free carnitine than milk of control sows [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
